title: Introduce CS_PACKAGE_DATE macro
message:
Introduce CS_PACKAGE_DATE macro

Defaults to __DATE__ if not set. This can be overriden, in order to set
a deterministic date on it, and thus one step closer to binary
reproducibility.

Fixes: #561

title: Add option to build the scanned synthesis opcodes
message:
Add option to build the scanned synthesis opcodes

Because these opcodes are non-free according to debian they need to strip
scansyn* from the sources. They also need a patch to remove the opcodes,
that needs to be refreshed on each new csound release.

With this option they can drop the patch and simply specify that scansyn
opcodes are not to be built.

title: This commit is the first one including a marginally working copy of csound-OSXâ€¦
message: This commit is the first one including a marginally working copy of csound-OSX and the accompany example project "Csound OSX Examples" which contains two examples from the csound-iOS project.  It plays sound, but does not have proper hooks to valueCacheable and crashes.

title: I have simplified CsoundObj by removing all the items from it that are hardwareâ€¦
message: I have simplified CsoundObj by removing all the items from it that are hardware specific to iOS.  All of the UI related code was moved to a CsoundUI object and the hardware motion code was moved to a CsoundMotion object.  This should allow the CsoundObj to be closer to being generic for use in OSX as well as iOS with fewer compiler directives and such.  I've also updated the manual slightly to reflect these new objects.

Bug #26: CsoundObj: modified getInputChannelPtr to require passing in the channelType (i.e. CSOUND_CONTROL_CHANNEL, CSOUND_AUDIO_CHANNEL); previously getInputChannelPtr was hardcoded for only control channels. This is a non-backwards compatible change.  To update previous project, add "controlChannelType.CSOUND_CONTROL_CHANNEL" when calling getInputChannelPtr.

* CsoundObj: added getOutputChannelPtr method

title: * Bug #26: CsoundObj.m: modified getInputChannelPtr and getOutputChannelPtr toâ€¦
message: * Bug #26: CsoundObj.m: modified getInputChannelPtr and getOutputChannelPtr to require passing in the channelType (i.e. CSOUND_CONTROL_CHANNEL, CSOUND_AUDIO_CHANNEL); previously getInputChannelPtr was hardcoded for only control channels and getOutputChannelPtr was hardcoded for only audio channels.  This is a non-backwards compatible change.  To update previous project, add "channelType:CSOUND_CONTROL_CHANNEL" when calling getInputChannelPtr and "channelType:CSOUND_AUDIO_CHANNEL" when calling getOutputCHannelPtr.

There is now a distinction between "internal" (i.e. [[k]) and "external" (i.e. k[][]) syntax for arrays.  Users and opcode writers should use k[][], while internally all checks and conversions are done automatically to internal syntax.

title: applied patch from Carlos Pita for Virtual Keyboard (Feature Request ID: 3425335)
message:
applied patch from Carlos Pita for Virtual Keyboard (Feature Request ID: 3425335)

1) Dropdown for choosing base octave (the one that starts with the virtual
key mapped to physical key Z). Default value is 5 which is backwards
compatible.

2) Shift-X mappings which add two octaves to X mappings for a total of 4
octaves playable from the physical keyboard (starting from selected base
octave).

3) Control-N / Control-Shift-N mappings to increment / decrement slider
for control N.

4) Mouse wheel now controls sliders.

title: Fixed bug in Windows build with MSVC. The code accessed FLTK flags as a valueâ€¦
message: Fixed bug in Windows build with MSVC. The code accessed FLTK flags as a value when the flags had not been initialized as a global variable. This caused an access violation in csoundModuleDestroy. The code has been changed to get the flags as a pointer, and only dereference the pointer if it is not null.

title: Fixed big bug in Windows widgets allocation. C++ struct was being allocated withâ€¦
message: Fixed big bug in Windows widgets allocation. C++ struct was being allocated with csound->Calloc() in the widget code itself. This is not necessary since the widget object is being called by Csound to manage its own memory. Furthermore it could never have worked. I replaced Csound memory management with new and delete, so that the constructors of the vectors in the structure would run and then the csoundModuleDestroy function would not crash by trying to iterator or clear uninitialied std::vector objects.

title: Fixed big bug in Windows widgets allocation. C++ struct was being allocated withâ€¦
message: Fixed big bug in Windows widgets allocation. C++ struct was being allocated with csound->Calloc() in the widget code itself. This is not necessary since the widget object is being called by Csound to manage its own memory. Furthermore it could never have worked. I replaced Csound memory management with new and delete, so that the constructors of the vectors in the structure would run and then the csoundModuleDestroy function would not crash by trying to iterator or clear uninitialied std::vector objects.

title: Added rudimentary shell script to generate SWIG lisp.
message:
Added rudimentary shell script to generate SWIG lisp.
The following MUST be added at the top of each generated .lisp file:

(defpackage :csound
    (:use :common-lisp :cffi))
(in-package :csound)

or :filebuilding as the case may be.

Also, variadic arguments are incorrectly handled by SWIG and must be replaced by &rest.
